### 10. How Routes Are Registered in app.ts

In `/src/app.ts`, routes are registered using:

```typescript
app.use("/posts", postsRouter);      // Posts endpoints under /posts prefix
app.use(commentsRouter);             // Comments endpoints at root (already have /posts/:id/comments paths)
```

This creates a two-tier routing structure:
1. **Posts Router** mounted at `/posts` prefix
   - Individual endpoints: `/`, `/:id`, `/:id` (PUT/DELETE), `:id` (POST)
   - Full paths: `GET /posts`, `GET /posts/1`, `POST /posts`, `PUT /posts/1`, `DELETE /posts/1`

2. **Comments Router** mounted at root but defines full paths internally
   - Full paths: `GET /posts/1/comments`, `POST /posts/1/comments`, `GET /comments/1`, `PUT /comments/1`, `DELETE /comments/1`

